In this article, President Trump speaks to the media in the Cabinet Room, discussing various topics including the appointment of Mark Esper as Secretary of Defense, the state of the military, and the situation in Syria. Trump expresses his desire to bring American soldiers back home and highlights the need for other nations, particularly European countries, to take responsibility for captured ISIS fighters. He also dismisses concerns about the second whistleblower and calls the impeachment inquiry a scam. Trump emphasizes the success of his presidency, citing strong poll numbers and fundraising.